// @description  Rebuilds the old Crazyparts category menu on the new site. Category data is baked in (snapshot 2026-06-13) so it no longer needs oldcrazyparts.com.au. Sections show as a 3-wide grid of equal-height columns, the filter searches every section, and an Edit mode lets you rename/add/remove sections and devices (saved in your browser). A Repair Parts / Accessories switch picks which filter is auto-applied after you click a model, and the product listing is bumped to PAGE_SIZE items per page. Every click stays on the new site via its own search. v1.5.1: launcher docks LEFT of the Apple tab and now self-heals on a heartbeat so React page-changes can't leave it missing.
